lead_paragraph: She has only recently entered the sport and, at age 28, is a relatively late bloomer. But just the fact that she is here is an accomplishment. Robin Umphrey of Huntington Beach, Calif., was about to become a police officer four years ago so she began training in a self-defense class. She tried taekwondo, became hooked, and after training with Roland Ferrer, the 1988 national champion, she is California's three-time state champion in the heavyweight division.

headline.main: Early Success for a Late Entry
